<section class="space-y-10">
  <div class="space-y-5">
    <p class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-zinc-500">Hydra Agent Runtime</p>
    <h1 class="max-w-3xl text-4xl font-semibold tracking-normal text-zinc-950 sm:text-5xl">
      A security-first control plane for specialized agents.
    </h1>
    <p class="max-w-2xl text-base leading-7 text-zinc-600">
      Hydra Agent is being split from Hydra-X as a clean runtime: workspaces, declarative
      agent packs, policy-gated tools, durable runs, and a flexible knowledge graph.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-2">
    <div class="rounded-lg border border-zinc-200 bg-white p-5 shadow-sm">
      <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-zinc-950">Runtime core</h2>
      <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-6 text-zinc-600">
        Workspaces, agents, conversations, runs, steps, providers, and tool policies are
        modeled as durable runtime state.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="rounded-lg border border-zinc-200 bg-white p-5 shadow-sm">
      <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-zinc-950">Knowledge graph</h2>
      <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-6 text-zinc-600">
        The former product graph direction becomes a neutral workspace knowledge graph for
        memories, evidence, artifacts, and orchestration context.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="rounded-lg border border-zinc-200 bg-white p-5 shadow-sm">
      <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-zinc-950">Least privilege</h2>
      <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-6 text-zinc-600">
        Agent packs and tool policies default to read-only operation. Sensitive actions need
        explicit grants, approvals, and audit trails.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="rounded-lg border border-zinc-200 bg-white p-5 shadow-sm">
      <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-zinc-950">Transparent orchestration</h2>
      <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-6 text-zinc-600">
        Supervisor agents plan, delegate, pause, recover, and reconcile work through visible
        run timelines rather than hidden prompt loops.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
